            <div class="solution-card">
                <h3>2. Healthcare Access: Saving Lives & Communities</h3>
                
                <h4><span class="category-label immediate">Immediate Win</span> Rural Emergency Response (Launch in 90 Days)</h4>
                <p><strong>Stop the Bleeding First:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Mobile Emergency Units (20 vehicles)</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Each unit: 1 nurse practitioner, 1 paramedic, diagnostic equipment</li>
                            <li>Coverage: 60 rural communities on rotating schedule</li>
                            <li>Services: Urgent care, chronic disease management, preventive care</li>
                            <li>Cost: $15M for vehicles and equipment, $8M annual operations</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Telehealth Emergency Network</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>iPads and hotspots for 10,000 high-risk patients</li>
                            <li>24/7 access to UMMC specialists</li>
                            <li>Remote monitoring for diabetes, heart disease, hypertension</li>
                            <li>Cost: $5M setup, $2M annual</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Pharmacy Desert Solution</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Mail-order prescription program for rural residents</li>
                            <li>Partner with Mississippi pharmacists for oversight</li>
                            <li>90-day supplies to reduce refill challenges</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="funding-box">
                    <strong>Immediate Funding Available:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>ARPA funds designated for rural health: $23M ready now</li>
                        <li>FCC Telehealth Program: $3M approved, awaiting deployment</li>
                        <li>HRSA Rural Health grants: $5M annual</li>
                        <li>Total Year 1: $31M fully funded</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="example-box">
                    <strong>South Carolina Mobile Success:</strong> Their mobile health program reached 45,000 rural residents in Year 1. Emergency room visits dropped 28%. Diabetes control improved in 67% of patients. Three rural hospitals stayed open because reduced ER burden improved finances. Cost per patient: $215 vs. $1,400 for ER visits.
                </div>
                
                <h4><span class="category-label strategic">Strategic Investment</span> Hospital Stabilization & Women's Health (Years 2-5)</h4>
                <p><strong>Rebuilding the Healthcare Infrastructure:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Rural Hospital Rescue Package</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Convert 10 struggling hospitals to Rural Emergency Hospitals (new Medicare designation)</li>
                            <li>Monthly facility payments of $270,000 from Medicare</li>
                            <li>5% payment increase for emergency services</li>
