                            <li>Doula and midwife training programs (200 new providers)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Community Health Worker Army</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Train and deploy 1,000 workers ($35,000 salary + benefits)</li>
                            <li>Each covers 250 high-risk residents</li>
                            <li>Home visits, medication compliance, appointment scheduling</li>
                            <li>Diabetes prevention program reaching 50,000 residents</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Medical Debt Relief Program</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Partner with RIP Medical Debt nonprofit</li>
                            <li>$10M state investment erases $1B in medical debt</li>
                            <li>Priority: Families under 200% poverty line</li>
                            <li>Affects 150,000 Mississippi families</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
