                <h3>3. Infrastructure Rebuild: Foundation for Growth</h3>
                
                <h4><span class="category-label immediate">Immediate Win</span> Jackson Water Crisis Resolution (6 Months)</h4>
                <p><strong>Emergency Action Plan:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Federal Emergency Management</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>EPA takes temporary control with $450M federal investment</li>
                            <li>Army Corps of Engineers oversees repairs</li>
                            <li>24/7 water quality monitoring and public reporting</li>
                            <li>Bottled water distribution continues until safe</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Immediate Repairs</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Replace pumps at O.B. Curtis plant: $25M</li>
                            <li>Fix water mains causing 40% water loss: $50M</li>
                            <li>Install backup systems: $35M</li>
                            <li>Emergency interconnections with nearby systems: $15M</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Workforce Development</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Train 100 water operators at $55,000 starting salary</li>
                            <li>Partner with Jackson State for water engineering program</li>
                            <li>Create apprenticeship pipeline with high schools</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="example-box">
                    <strong>Flint's Recovery Blueprint:</strong> After their water crisis, Flint received $650M in federal and state aid. They replaced 10,000 lead service lines, rebuilt treatment plants, and haven't had a violation in 3 years. Key lesson: Federal oversight and funding worked where local resources failed.
                </div>
                
                <h4><span class="category-label strategic">Strategic Investment</span> Connecting Mississippi - Broadband & Roads (Years 2-5)</h4>
                <p><strong>21st Century Infrastructure:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Broadband Revolution</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Create Mississippi Broadband Authority with $1.2B federal funds</li>
                            <li>Fiber to every community over 500 people: $800M</li>
                            <li>Low-orbit satellite for remote areas: $100M</li>
                            <li>Free WiFi in all public buildings and parks: $50M</li>
                            <li>Digital literacy training for 100,000 residents: $20M</li>
                            <li>"Dig Once" policy: Install conduit during all road work</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Bridge & Road Rescue</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Fix 500 most dangerous bridges: $2B over 4 years</li>
                            <li>Repave 3,000 miles of critical roads: $1.5B</li>
                            <li>Create Mississippi Infrastructure Bank for local matching funds</li>
                            <li>Weight station upgrades to preserve road investments: $25M</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Rural Water Systems</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Consolidate 150 failing small systems into 30 regional systems</li>
                            <li>Professional management reducing costs 40%</li>
                            <li>EPA grants for consolidation: $300M available</li>
                            <li>State revolving loan fund: $200M at 0% interest</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="funding-box">
                    <strong>Infrastructure Funding Secured:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Infrastructure Investment and Jobs Act: $3.6B for Mississippi</li>
                        <li>BEAD broadband program: $1.2B allocated</li>
                        <li>Highway Trust Fund: $650M annually</li>
                        <li>EPA water infrastructure: $429M available</li>
                        <li>USDA rural development: $200M annually</li>
                        <li>Total 4-year funding: $4.8B available now</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="example-box">
                    <strong>Tennessee's Broadband Win:</strong> Tennessee invested $500M in rural broadband, connecting 95% of residents in 5 years. Results: 13,000 new remote jobs, $1.2B in economic growth, students' test scores increased 8%, and telehealth saved rural hospitals. Every $1 invested returned $3.50 in economic activity.
