            <div class="solution-card">
                <h3>5. Tax Reform: Fair System That Works</h3>
                
                <h4><span class="category-label transformational">Transformational Change</span> Grocery Tax Elimination (5-Year Phase-Out)</h4>
                <p><strong>Putting Money Back in Family Budgets:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Phase-Out Schedule</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Year 1: Reduce from 7% to 5.5% (saves families $156/year)</li>
                            <li>Year 2: Drop to 4% (saves $312/year)</li>
                            <li>Year 3: Reduce to 2.5% (saves $468/year)</li>
                            <li>Year 4: Lower to 1% (saves $624/year)</li>
                            <li>Year 5: Complete elimination (saves $780/year)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Revenue Replacement Plan</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Close corporate tax loopholes: $125M annually</li>
                            <li>Online sales tax collection: $200M annually</li>
                            <li>Luxury tax on boats/planes over $250K: $30M</li>
                            <li>Cannabis tax (if legalized): $100M annually</li>
                            <li>Economic growth from increased spending: $75M</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Low-Income Protection</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Quarterly rebates for families under $50,000</li>
                            <li>SNAP recipients get immediate full elimination</li>
                            <li>Senior citizens receive monthly credits</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="example-box">
                    <strong>Real Family Impact - Pearl Family of Four:</strong> The Johnsons spend $800/month on groceries ($9,600/year). Current tax: $672. After elimination: $0. That's two months of car payments, or school supplies and clothes for three kids, or emergency fund for home repairs. Multiply by 200,000 families: $134M staying in local economy.
                </div>
                
