                        <ul>
                            <li>Drought-resistant crop research at Mississippi State</li>
                            <li>Precision agriculture reducing water use 30%</li>
                            <li>Cover crop incentives preventing soil erosion</li>
                            <li>Alternative crops for changing climate (pecans, fruits)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Clean Energy Transition</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Solar gardens in every county: Community ownership</li>
                            <li>Wind farms in northwestern counties: 2,000 jobs</li>
                            <li>Battery manufacturing for grid storage: 1,500 jobs</li>
                            <li>Weatherization for 100,000 homes: Save $400/year each</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="funding-box">
                    <strong>Climate Funding Available:</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Gulf of Mexico restoration funds: $750M over 15 years</li>
                        <li>FEMA hazard mitigation: $200M</li>
                        <li>USDA climate-smart agriculture: $100M</li>
                        <li>DOE clean energy programs: $300M</li>
                        <li>EPA environmental justice grants: $50M</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="example-box">
                    <strong>Biloxi's Green Infrastructure:</strong> After Katrina, Biloxi rebuilt with resilience. Their living shoreline reduced storm surge 70% during Hurricane Ida. Green infrastructure captured 2 million gallons of stormwater. Solar panels on public buildings saved $400,000 annually. The city is now a model for climate adaptation, attracting $50M in federal grants.
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="solution-card">
                <h3>8. Community Safety & Support</h3>
                
                <h4><span class="category-label immediate">Immediate Win</span> Domestic Violence Response</h4>
                <p><strong>Safety Nets That Save Lives:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Emergency Shelter Expansion</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Add 500 emergency beds statewide: $15M</li>
                            <li>Pet-friendly shelters (many stay in danger for pets)</li>
                            <li>Transitional housing: 6 months support</li>
                            <li>Rural safe houses in 20 counties</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Legal Protection Fast-Track</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>24-hour protection order processing</li>
                            <li>Free attorneys for all victims</li>
                            <li>Court advocates in every county</li>
                            <li>GPS monitoring for all protective orders</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Economic Empowerment</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Emergency funds: $2,000 for immediate relocation</li>
                            <li>Job training specifically for survivors</li>
                            <li>Childcare assistance during court proceedings</li>
                            <li>Credit repair and financial counseling</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="example-box">
                    <strong>Madison County Success:</strong> After implementing comprehensive DV response, domestic homicides dropped 60% in three years. The key? Combining emergency housing, legal help, and economic support. Sarah, a survivor, says: "The job training saved my life. I could finally leave because I knew I could support my kids."
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="solution-card">
                <h3>9. Government Accountability</h3>
                
                <h4><span class="category-label immediate">Immediate Win</span> Transparency Revolution</h4>
                <p><strong>Your Money, Your Right to Know:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Open Checkbook Mississippi</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Every payment over $100 online in real-time</li>
                            <li>Searchable by vendor, agency, purpose</li>
                            <li>Contract details and performance metrics</li>
                            <li>Automatic alerts for suspicious patterns</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Inspector General Network</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Independent IGs for major agencies</li>
                            <li>Whistleblower rewards up to $100,000</li>
                            <li>Quarterly public reports required</li>
                            <li>Criminal referral authority</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Citizen Oversight Boards</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Random selection like jury duty</li>
                            <li>Review all contracts over $1 million</li>
                            <li>Veto power over suspicious deals</li>
                            <li>Public hearings streamed online</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="example-box">
                    <strong>After Welfare Scandal Reform:</strong> Following the $94 million welfare scandal, new oversight prevented $12M in questionable spending in Year 1 alone. An anonymous tip line caught three fraudulent contracts. Public trust surveys show 40% increase in confidence. "Sunshine really is the best disinfectant," says ethics director.
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <section class="section">
            <h2>Understanding the Money: Real Numbers, Real Solutions</h2>
            
            <div class="stat-highlight">
                <h4>Mississippi's Current Budget Reality</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Total State Budget:</strong> $7.6 billion (FY 2024)</li>
                    <li><strong>Education:</strong> $3.95 billion (52%)</li>
                    <li><strong>Health/Human Services:</strong> $1.9 billion (25%)</li>
                    <li><strong>Corrections:</strong> $608 million (8%)</li>
                    <li><strong>Transportation:</strong> $456 million (6%)</li>
                    <li><strong>All Other:</strong> $684 million (9%)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="funding-box">
