            <p style="margin-top: 2rem;"><strong>The Bottom Line:</strong> Mississippi has access to over $8 billion in federal funds already allocated but not yet spent. Combined with strategic state investments and public-private partnerships, we can transform our state without breaking the budget. Every dollar invested in education returns $7 in economic growth. Every dollar in infrastructure returns $3. This isn't spendingâ€”it's investing in Mississippi's future.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section class="section" id="resources">
            <h2>Resources & Community Action</h2>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
                Change happens when communities come together. Here's how you can make a difference today:
            </p>
            
            <div class="solution-card">
                <h3>Get Help Now - Emergency Resources</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Crisis Hotline:</strong> Call or text 988 for mental health emergencies</li>
                    <li><strong>Domestic Violence:</strong> 1-800-898-3234 (24/7 confidential)</li>
                    <li><strong>Food Emergency:</strong> Call 211 for nearest food bank</li>
                    <li><strong>Utility Shutoff:</strong> LIHEAP assistance: 1-800-421-0589</li>
                    <li><strong>Medical Emergency Without Insurance:</strong> Federally Qualified Health Centers: findahealthcenter.hrsa.gov</li>
                    <li><strong>Housing Crisis:</strong> Mississippi Home Corporation: 601-718-4636</li>
                    <li><strong>Legal Aid:</strong> Mississippi Legal Services: 1-800-498-1804</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="solution-card">
                <h3>Join the Movement - Local Action</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Town Halls:</strong> Find schedules at your city/county websites</li>
                    <li><strong>School Board Meetings:</strong> Usually first Tuesday monthly - public comment welcome</li>
                    <li><strong>Community Organizations:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Mississippi NAACP: Racial justice advocacy</li>
                            <li>Mississippi Center for Justice: Legal reform</li>
                            <li>Parents for Public Schools: Education advocacy</li>
                            <li>Working Together Jackson: Community organizing</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Volunteer Opportunities:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Habitat for Humanity: Build homes (habitatms.org)</li>
                            <li>Literacy volunteers: Teach reading (literacymidsouth.org)</li>
                            <li>Food banks: Sort and distribute (feedingamerica.org)</li>
                            <li>Senior centers: Companion programs</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="solution-card">
                <h3>Make Your Voice Heard</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Contact Your Representatives:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Find them: legislature.ms.gov/legislators/</li>
                            <li>Call during session: Most effective</li>
                            <li>Email template: "I'm a constituent in [City] and I support/oppose..."</li>
                            <li>Visit local offices: Face-to-face matters most</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Start or Sign Petitions:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Ballot initiatives: Need 106,000 signatures</li>
                            <li>Local petitions: Often need just 1,000</li>
                            <li>Online platforms: Change.org/mississippi</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Media Engagement:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Letters to editor: 200-word limit most papers</li>
                            <li>Call radio shows: Local talk radio wants callers</li>
                            <li>Social media: Tag representatives and use #MSLeg</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="solution-card">
                <h3>Resources for Businesses</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Small Business Development:</strong> Mississippi SBDC - Free consulting (msbdc.org)</li>
                    <li><strong>Loans and Grants:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Mississippi Development Authority: Low-interest loans</li>
                            <li>USDA Rural Development: Grants up to $500,000</li>
                            <li>Minority Business Alliance: Special programs</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Training Programs:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>WIN Job Centers: Free workforce training</li>
                            <li>Community colleges: Customized business training</li>
                            <li>SCORE mentors: Free business advice</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
